---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");

const agentNeverSees = [
  "The actual provider API key (Anthropic, OpenAI, etc.) backing each request.",
  "Long-lived GitHub App private keys, OAuth secrets, or PATs.",
  "Static-provider master tokens or any secret declared in a BrokerPolicy.",
  "The MITM CA private key issued per run.",
];

const operatorCanSee = [
  "Every credential issuance, with provider, run identity, and outcome.",
  "Every egress connection, validated against the run's allowlist.",
  "Every authorization substitution, with the request envelope (not body) and outcome.",
  "Per-run AuditEvent objects with TTL-controlled retention.",
];

const supplyChain = [
  "Every image is built reproducibly from the monorepo and signed with Cosign (keyless, Sigstore).",
  "SBOMs are attached to every release artifact and verifiable from the registry.",
  "Helm charts are published as OCI artifacts to GHCR with the same signing posture.",
  "Every push to main is published under :main and an immutable :main-<sha> tag for pinning.",
];
---
<BaseLayout title="Security" pathname="/security">
  <article class="container" style="padding-block: var(--space-8);">
    <header class="prose">
      <h1>Security model</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Paddock is shaped by the assumption that the agent inside the container
        is untrusted code. The security boundary is the line a credential, a
        token, or an unscoped network connection cannot cross.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>Threat model in three paragraphs</h2>
      <p>
        Coding agents are large, opaque programs that accept arbitrary natural
        language input and produce arbitrary side effects. Treat them as
        untrusted code that you nevertheless want to run useful work for you.
        Containment, not trust, is the design centre.
      </p>
      <p>
        Three actors define the security boundary: the operator (writes
        policy), the platform (enforces it), and the agent (lives inside it).
        Anything an operator declares — credentials, allowlisted FQDNs,
        permissible repos, branch namespaces — becomes an admission contract
        that the broker validates and the proxy enforces.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the full detail, see
        <a href="https://github.com/tjorri/paddock/blob/main/docs/security/threat-model.md">
          docs/security/threat-model.md</a> in the repo.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The boundary in one diagram</h2>
      <div class="diagram-slot" aria-label="Security boundary diagram (placeholder)">
        <!-- Diagram lands in Task 9 -->
        <p class="diagram-placeholder">Diagram pending — see Task 9.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>What the agent never sees</h2>
      <ul>{agentNeverSees.map((it) => <li>{it}</li>)}</ul>
    </section>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>What the operator can see</h2>
      <ul>{operatorCanSee.map((it) => <li>{it}</li>)}</ul>
      <p>
        Run <code>kubectl paddock audit --run &lt;name&gt;</code> to enumerate the
        AuditEvents for any run.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>Supply chain</h2>
      <ul>{supplyChain.map((it) => <li>{it}</li>)}</ul>
      <p>Verify a published image:</p>
      <pre><code>{`cosign verify ghcr.io/tjorri/paddock-manager:v0.4.0 \\
  --certificate-identity-regexp='^https://github\\.com/tjorri/paddock/' \\
  --certificate-oidc-issuer='https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com'`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>Recent security work</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/tjorri/paddock/blob/main/docs/security/2026-04-25-v0.4-audit-findings.md">
            v0.4 audit findings (Phase 1)</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/tjorri/paddock/blob/main/docs/security/2026-04-25-v0.4-test-gaps.md">
            v0.4 test-gap analysis</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          The Phase 2 series (a–g) on the
          <a href="https://github.com/tjorri/paddock/commits/main">main commit log</a>:
          P0 hotfix, audit completeness, adversarial test coverage, carry-over fixes,
          pod-spec hardening, per-run intermediate CA, substitute-auth hygiene.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    .lead { font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-text-muted); }
    .diagram-slot {
      margin: var(--space-5) 0;
      padding: var(--space-7);
      border: 1px dashed var(--color-rule);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      background: var(--color-bg-2);
      text-align: center;
    }
    .diagram-placeholder {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      font-style: italic;
    }
    pre {
      background: var(--color-bg-2);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      padding: var(--space-4);
      overflow-x: auto;
      max-width: var(--prose-max-w);
    }
    pre code { background: transparent; }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
